name: Los Angeles
absentee_method: Released as a separate subtotal as first report of the night
nyt_race_description_race: Katie Hill, a Democratic newcomer, won this seat in 2018 as part of California’s “blue wave.” But her resignation a year ago reopened the field to a wide range of contenders, including Mike Garcia, a Republican former military pilot, who easily beat Christy Smith, a Democratic member of the State Assembly, in a May special election. That win for the seat was just on a temporary basis, though, and the two are now fighting a rematch.
poll_display_race: Polls close at 11 p.m. Eastern time.
expectations_text_race: All active registered voters were sent mail ballots, and late-arriving mail ballots and provisional ballots will be counted in the days and weeks after the election.
expectations_text_short_race: All active registered voters were sent mail ballots, and late-arriving mail ballots and provisional ballots will be counted in the days and weeks after the election.
